Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.80,0:00:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"A ravaged country still has \Nits untouched nature. {chinese poem "springtime"; http://www.kangin.or.jp/learning/text/chinese/k_B1_025.html}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.97,0:01:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Spring has arrived in the capital and the grass is lush and green." {no idea what to make of 城春, seems to be some chinese city}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.38,0:01:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This poem really hits home for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.27,0:01:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, a little further down this road is the Ryogo Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.94,0:01:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking for Masuda-san's house, \Nthe son of the Nasu Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.89,0:01:19.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 1946 \NRyogo Village, Nasu County, Tochigi Prefecture
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.36,0:01:19.35,NarTop,,0,0,0,,The missionary work in post-war rural Japan had begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.90,0:01:23.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda, with a group of his followers, traveled to Ryogo Village in Tochigi Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.65,0:01:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.66,0:01:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.11,0:01:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"Toda Josei is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.11,0:01:31.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toda Josei is coming!\NGrand Lecture on the Lotus Sutra\NTime: September 22nd, 2 p.m.\NLocation: Ryogo Public School
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.06,0:01:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Lecture on the Lotus Sutra?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.23,0:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody here would know who Toda Josei is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.05,0:01:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At best, the locals would be wondering, \N"Now, what kind of bum is that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.62,0:01:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.77,0:01:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for coming here all the way from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.26,0:01:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been waiting for you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.80,0:01:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They say you can't fight a war if you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.35,0:01:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, please help yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.07,0:01:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a bunch! We will!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.62,0:02:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.46,0:02:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't just come here to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be meeting the people soon, \Nwe need to be fully prepared by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.46,0:02:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.21,0:02:25.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,Ryogo Public School
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.63,0:02:30.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the Lotus Sutra Grand Lecture \Nheld at the public school in Ryogo Village,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.63,0:02:27.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,Main Hall {actually "sewing room" but idk why they keep calling all the important places in schools that; 裁縫室}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.63,0:02:30.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,Lotus Sutra Grand Lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.91,0:02:32.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as many as 80 residents
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.77,0:02:35.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of all ages and origins, from here and the neighboring villages, gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.86,0:02:37.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was an extremely successful lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.61,0:02:39.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even though people
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.91,0:02:44.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,were very confused to hear about Buddhism for the first time in their lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:47.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,everyone was listening intently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, I would like to ask Toda Josei-sensei to conclude the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.21,0:02:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,'Tis that old pops dey call Toda Josei? {speaks with a very rural lilt}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.47,0:03:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard there was a sect called Soka Gakkai or something, who revere him as the great teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.40,0:03:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Never heard of those Soka Gakkai coots.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.42,0:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How can our nation, crushed in battle, revive itself as a truly peace-loving nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The only path towards achieving that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.25,0:03:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is by grounding our way of life \Nin true religion and correct ideology.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.64,0:03:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me that the teachings and philosophy of Nichiren Daishonin fit that bill perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.99,0:03:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear friends, it appears to me that our lecture today was your first introduction to Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.82,0:03:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But now that you know what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for the happiness of your families and yourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as for the peaceful future of Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.70,0:03:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray that you waste no time in letting the great mercy of Buddha into your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.32,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Think they'll come?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... Old habits run deep in these parts... {/people are unlikely to change their ways}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.87,0:03:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll definitely come! \NThink of the reaction we got from this audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.09,0:04:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.98,0:04:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.45,0:04:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See? They did come!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.02,0:04:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.19,0:04:15.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin's Scriptures{no idea what the characters are; feel free to omit if too hard to typeset}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.21,0:04:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, did you decide to give Buddhism a shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.67,0:04:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I want to try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.16,0:04:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,this person also wishes to join.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.17,0:04:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Congratulations! \NWe can achieve a lot together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for having me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:46.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nihon Shogakkan
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.35,0:04:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, it's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.56,0:04:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.83,0:04:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Izumida-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.22,0:05:01.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Izumida Hiroshi was finally repatriated from abroad three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.06,0:05:03.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was Izumida Tame's husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.26,0:05:06.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,dispatched as a soldier \Nto the battlefields of the Southern Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.80,0:05:08.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was a strange experience -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.50,0:05:13.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,returning home without firing a single bullet, \Nor seeing a single man die in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? You look unhappy. \NDid you quarrel with your wife again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.09,0:05:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.72,0:05:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So what did you fight over?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.50,0:05:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I still haven't found a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.11,0:05:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I come home, she reproaches me for "dawdling around all day."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.66,0:05:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not very encouraging...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.81,0:05:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you resorted to violence?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.08,0:05:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.27,0:05:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Hiroshi, that won't do. \NIt's simply unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.79,0:05:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When a man is cornered by a woman, \Nhe's immediately compelled to use violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.50,0:05:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not the path of a Lotus Sutra follower.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I am making every effort to find a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But she doesn't seem to recognize that at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.46,0:05:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. But let's not forget that women also have to face the harsh reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She can't treat you as a real man unless you can give her a sense of security in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, more than anything else, we need to revolutionize our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.53,0:06:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fight only starts after we achieve that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.33,0:06:19.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Before long, Izumida got a job at a small publishing company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:22.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the time, people all across the country were destitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:25.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Food was still in very short supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:28.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even getting a bowl of simple  broth was extremely difficult. {/suiton - in a sense "very primitive and cheap food"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.32,0:06:28.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Rationing center {食料支給人}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.83,0:06:31.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, labor disputes triggered by the announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.60,0:06:34.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of 130,000 layoffs by Japan National Railways
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:38.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,gradually intensified, \Nplunging society into a turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.83,0:06:32.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Protest against layoffs! {馘首絶\N対反対}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.78,0:06:34.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Strikes at Toshiba {東芝罷業決行}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.81,0:06:39.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Control of national media {放送の國家管理}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:42.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,November 17, 1946 \NKanda Education Hall {1946年(昭和21年)11月17日神田・教育会館}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:45.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,Education Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.80,0:06:48.76,NarTop,,0,0,0,,On November 17, 1946,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:51.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,Memorial service for the third anniversary of the first president Makiguchi's death {牧口初代会長 三回忌法要}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:53.81,NarTop,,0,0,0,,for the third anniversary of the first president Makiguchi's death, a grand memorial service
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.81,0:06:57.29,NarTop,,0,0,0,,was held at the Kanda Educational Hall. \NIt was like an organization-wide funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.71,0:07:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was through your vast \Nand boundless mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that you lead me to the imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.93,0:07:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, I was able to read this passage from the Lotus Sutra,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.85,0:07:22.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,In all the planes of Buddha's existence, the bond between mentor and disciple is eternal {在在諸仏土 常与師俱生}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.93,0:07:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,"In all the planes of Buddha's existence, the bond between mentor and disciple is eternal."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.35,0:07:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was what inspired me to devote my life entirely to the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, \NI, a worthless idiot,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.24,0:07:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,am still going strong on your path \Nof fulfilling the mission of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I am determined to become worthy of your praise by the time we meet at the Vulture Peak. {mountain in india that's allegedly a stamping ground for buddhas; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vulture_Peak}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your loyal disciple Toda Josei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:58.92,NarTop,,0,0,0,,After an hour's break, \Nat that very same venue,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.54,0:08:02.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,The first Soka Gakkai General Meeting {第1回創価学会総会}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.92,0:08:02.59,NarTop,,0,0,0,,the first postwar Soka Gakkai general meeting was held.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.23,0:08:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to rewards or punishments,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.23,0:08:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unreasonable to think that only Buddha has the privilege to grant them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.29,0:08:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Take, for example, humans, who live their whole lives expecting rewards or punishments.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:20.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda used familiar examples to provide simple and humane explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.20,0:08:24.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He preached the great merits of Buddha \Nin a way that anyone would understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.44,0:08:28.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He talked about the mission of the Common Path\Nto build a land of peace and happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.09,0:08:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I dedicated my entire life to Buddha \Nand to the great cause of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.80,0:08:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My hope is that those who share my determination
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,will follow me to the end of the Earth. \NWhat do you think, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll follow wherever you take us, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a great future ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.23,0:08:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai's operations are going to speed up tremendously now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.61,0:08:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens, \Nwe'll be fearless!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.51,0:08:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes the first general meeting of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.45,0:09:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Look at how you've grown, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.32,0:09:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? The beautiful Nasu sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.46,0:09:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, thank you for\Nthe wonderful meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.31,0:09:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today, my faith is unshakeable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fight tooth and nail \Nfor the Common Path!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Today marks a new start for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.07,0:09:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei would have been happy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.73,0:09:48.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After the first general meeting, Toda's lectures on the Lotus Sutra and Nichiren's writings
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:52.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays \Nwere growing ever more popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.84,0:09:55.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In addition to roundtable discussions held on Sunday,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.80,0:10:01.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,extra discussions were also regularly held on Tuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the true nirvana
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.14,0:10:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is only achieved by attaining the Buddhahood, the highest state of life. {no idea what to make of 涌現 / yugen - it's only used in a couple of soka's works and comes from Chinese, it seems; possible translation is "emergence"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.10,0:10:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The implicit faith in Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism is instrumental for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.73,0:10:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also very important to pray to the Great Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.00,0:10:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two key steps are our plan for turning Japan into a Buddhist land of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.45,0:10:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A load of bull! \NYou're all charlatans!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Building a Buddhist country?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.95,0:10:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sweet talk won't work. \NI'm not buying this bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him talk. Let us hear \Neverything he has to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.12,0:10:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think is a lie and what isn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.31,0:10:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd all like to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.13,0:10:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit shitting me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.01,0:10:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We, the common people, have been tricked for as long as I remember myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.77,0:10:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"Emperor’s Army."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"Invincible Navy."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:10:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Divine right." {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hakk%C5%8D_ichiu - maybe "mandate of heaven" but that'll probably create confusion}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"I want nothing but victory." {Another WW2 slogan, supposedly composed by an 11 year old girl - literally "I don't wish for anything until we win"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.97,0:11:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Humph. How sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I also fell for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.64,0:11:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,joined a pilot school {actually "Yokaren" is a Japanese abbreviation for “Naval Aviator Preparatory Course Trainee.”}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.15,0:11:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and ended up in the kamikaze corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.11,0:11:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We sincerely believed that if our homeland of Japan would benefit from our death,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then we should go meet our death happily!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.76,0:11:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do we see now? \NDespite our best efforts, it lies in ruins!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When I came to my senses and reflected calmly on what I was doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.89,0:11:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized everyone had been bullshitting me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.77,0:11:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were young, we'd dance to just about anyone's merry tune!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.33,0:11:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep saying that you were fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.19,0:11:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But before you opened your eyes, you sincerely believed it all, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.29,0:11:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I did believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.16,0:11:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed it with all my heart. \NThat's what angers me the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.12,0:11:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,As your experience demonstrates us, \Nblind faith may become a terrifying weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.65,0:11:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Scarier than anything we've seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.88,0:12:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,People who believe faulty notions \Nare bound to fall into the depths of despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.34,0:12:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These are not my own words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.51,0:12:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A Buddhist monk
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.32,0:12:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin spelled out these universal truths 700 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.84,0:12:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you are scared of the very thought \Nof believing in something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.98,0:12:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I understand your heart's drive to never be fooled again very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.85,0:12:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.48,0:12:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what you also need to consider now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.95,0:12:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is whether or not there exists something worth believing with all your heart at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In conclusion, I'll say that Nichiren Daishonin
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.64,0:12:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,worked to make people happy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.05,0:12:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,by building a peaceful nation and society, grounded in rightful convictions and religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.65,0:12:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He preached the Buddhist teachings of Nam Myoho Renge Kyo with great conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So what will Daishonin-sama gain by deceiving you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.75,0:12:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is worth believing at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if not this Dharma? {probably means lotus sutra}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.19,0:13:06.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To save one young man... \NTo save a single common man,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.49,0:13:11.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda and other Soka Gakkai members worked hard to preach Daishonin's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:15.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As Toda was running around town from one roundtable discussion to another,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.93,0:13:17.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the society...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.25,0:13:19.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,Strikes! \NAll go on a strike! {etc}\NToshiba union strikes {東芝労組ストテ中}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.74,0:13:21.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,Joint Struggle to Begin Next Month\NEstablish a unification committee {來月から共闘へ\N統一委員會を設く - no idea what this is about, probably establishment of trade unions?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.32,0:13:22.61,Sign,,0,0,0,,All government and public sector labor unions declare joint struggle\NUltimatum expires by the 7th {全官公晓労組が\N共同闘争を宣言\N七日までに回答要}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.61,0:13:26.04,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yoshida-san, stop it!! {吉田サンヤメテヨ!!}{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shigeru_Yoshida}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.97,0:13:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.08,0:13:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have any questions left, \Nfeel free to ask. Any questions at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.54,0:13:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I was recently elected
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.82,0:13:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as a member of the conflict resolving committee of my company's labor union. {lit: struggle committee - responsible for planning and executing dispute plans during a labor dispute, issuing strike orders and taking measures, and managing dispute funds.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.97,0:13:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,People are struggling to make ends meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With inflation raging, \Nand living standards deteriorating,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.36,0:13:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, a direct social reform \Nis the most pressing issue
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.86,0:13:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:13:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Maybe he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.52,0:14:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.39,0:14:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, faith is important for our ultimate happiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.83,0:14:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe it's me who doesn't understand how you feel?! {unsure: 君たちの心が分からない私だと思うのか!}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.73,0:14:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.90,0:14:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My sweet disciples are fighting hard for their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you, my dear ones, \Nsay that you need me to be there for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.82,0:14:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be at the forefront of demonstrations and strikes, waving red flags and whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you think that will solve everything, you're mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.90,0:14:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look at it from the perspective of the Mystic Law,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this is only a fraction, \Na hundredth part of the problem. {unsure: 妙法による本源的な解決からみれば 何分の一 何百分の一のものでしかない}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.57,0:14:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's an economic battle \Nor a political battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.71,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the end, a compromise will be reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.92,0:14:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are more serious problems that cannot be resolved like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.43,0:14:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Human destiny and karma, \Nthe flaws and shortcomings of an individual,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.32,0:14:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,domestic strife,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.33,0:14:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,physical and mental illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.32,0:15:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There are far more problems \Nthat cannot be solved by a settlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.58,0:15:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we look at society, the public,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.33,0:15:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we would subdivide them into workers, bosses, and employers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, it all starts with an individual, \Nand ends with one. {/one human being is the source of all, and he is the conclusion}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.81,0:15:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My point is, we must approach this problem fundamentally, focusing on the individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings me to the importance of the law \Nfor solving this problem as a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.08,0:15:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That can only be achieved through the great religion which emphasizes the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.77,0:15:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fight had only recently found its comfortable pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But a time of tremendous \Nturmoil is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The people have yet to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.45,0:15:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to appreciate Daishonin's Buddhism on a profound level.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.29,0:15:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That time will come for sure. \NUntil then, let's all keep going strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.35,0:15:42.37,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,The new secondary school system will start on the 17th\NDesignated schools are now co-educational\NPrivate schools with prestigious schools too{新制中學十七日發足\N指定校は男女共學\N私立有名校は映}{context: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Educational_reform_in_occupied_Japan}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.30,0:15:50.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,April 1st: The 6-3 system is implemented \NNew junior high school system begins as compulsory education {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/6%E2%80%933_school_system}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.07,0:15:49.36,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Society was becoming increasingly anxious \Nabout inflation spiraling out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.36,0:15:52.64,NarTop,,0,0,0,,A new movement toward democratization was also actively budding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.10,0:15:54.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,May 3rd: The Constitution of Japan comes into force, ushering in a new era for Japan {5月3日 「日本国憲法」施行新生日本の歴史が開かれる}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.70,0:15:57.35,NarTop,,0,0,0,,Even at the Soka Gakkai meeting led by Toda...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.66,0:16:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.83,0:16:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.63,0:16:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like you to come to Kamata for a roundtable discussion in July.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In July? Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.63,0:16:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to go, \Nbut my schedule is already packed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How about August 14th?\NThat's when I'll be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.89,0:16:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sounds good.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's tell him about the roundtable discussion today, shall we, Sakata-san? {unsure: 酒田さん 今日は何としても座談会のことを言いましょう}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But I gotta say, when I look at those books at Yamamoto-kun's place,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.45,0:16:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always at a loss for words... {kiridasu - means "to come up with a sharp thing to say/smart repartee"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.50,0:16:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Carlyle, Nietzsche, Byron, and Heine, you mean that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was completely overwhelmed \Nwhen I first went there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.98,0:16:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's even more so for me. \NI've heard the names before, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,His shelves are full of books \Nthat I've never read before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.60,0:16:53.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.55,0:16:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you came to see Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.58,0:16:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait a moment. \NI believe he should be home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. And welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.95,0:17:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, here I am again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly. Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.12,0:17:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really manage to hold on to all those books throughout the war, Yamamoto-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all. \NLike I said the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,everything burned down in the air raid, \Nonly the dolls survived. {here's to hoping Ohina-sama is not a name of some obscure book}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.19,0:17:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I collected all these by making the rounds at used bookstores.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. But it must've cost a fortune, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.13,0:17:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.54,0:17:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear these "Notes on the Theory of Life"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.29,0:17:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,gained a lot of traction lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.27,0:17:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It seems that the news of the author, Miki Kiyoshi, dying in prison put it in the spotlight. {/served as a trigger}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.73,0:17:51.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun seems to be a huge philosophy buff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:53.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,You can't talk to him about anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:56.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I've never studied philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.53,0:17:58.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,What clever quip can I offer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.53,0:18:02.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,This pile of books \Nseems outright intimidating... {it's not in quot. marks because it's not a quip, he just says "I can't even imagine where to start with this mountain of books."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.53,0:18:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, there are also my classmates Morishita-kun, Yamada-kun, and Ishii-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.84,0:18:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All lost their homes in an air raid. \NMaybe you know where to find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.80,0:18:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.05,0:18:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After my home burned down, I ended up sponging off my aunt at Magome.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Once this place was finally vacated, I returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Back then, everyone had to occupy themselves with their own survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, would you look at the time! \NI need to return and help prepare dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.82,0:18:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for bothering you for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.52,0:18:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, by the way, Yamamoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be discussing philosophy \Nat my house on the night of the 14th.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.79,0:18:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.03,0:18:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Philosophy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we'll talk about the philosophy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.41,0:18:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Bergsonian, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:18:59.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,Bergsonian? \NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the guest lecturer? {/what kind of professor is coming?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.79,0:19:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei Toda Josei. \NHe's amazing, so make sure to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.79,0:19:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda Josei... \NIs he a philosopher?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He's will talk about a philosophy that fundamentally clarifies the phenomenon of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.02,0:19:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come pick you up. \NCome on, join us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.24,0:19:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose... \NI see no harm in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.87,0:19:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta see it. \NI'll come to get you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay... I'll be waiting, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.89,0:19:35.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,August 14, 1947.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.71,0:19:42.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The time of the first meeting between Toda Josei and Yamamoto Shinichi came on this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:44.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Mikawa {三川}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.06,0:19:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rather than perform ten thousand prayers, we should eliminate this one..." {the end of chapter 4 of Risshøankokuron}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.55,0:19:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a legendary amount of courage to say something like that to a ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.49,0:20:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,From shogunal regents of all ranks \Nto the common people,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.60,0:20:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone respected and worshipped Amitabha during the Kamakura period.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.72,0:20:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin alone vilified this blind faith in Nenbutsu prayers. {check my notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.31,0:20:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything, he determined those Nenbutsu prayers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.79,0:20:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the prime source \Nof people's unhappiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.55,0:20:23.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,It seems he is talking about Buddhism, \Nnot the philosophy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.34,0:20:25.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,How deep are these people's convictions?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Daishonin concluded his work on Rissho Ankokuron 700 years ago. {notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.70,0:20:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say it's like he left a note for the present day us, the defeated nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.34,0:20:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,First as an individual, \Nthen as a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually as a country, unless we solve this by returning to the Buddha Dharma,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.87,0:20:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll never start on our path to Buddhahood. {lit: nothing will ever start - no clue what he means, maybe "nothing good will come our way"; 個人であれ 一家であれまた一国であれこの仏法哲理に立ち返って問題を解決しない限り一切のことは始まらないのです}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.90,0:20:53.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Why does he look at me so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.48,0:20:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to eliminate all misery and tragedy from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.14,0:21:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My way of achieving that is the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.46,0:21:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, will you join me on this path?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.59,0:21:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.59,0:21:04.29,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.29,0:21:05.48,Overlap,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:11.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is amazing! \NWhy does it resonate with me so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I brought Yamamoto Shinichi-san with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.50,0:21:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He was my classmate \Nin elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.52,0:21:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Come closer, young man. \NWhat's the good of being all the way back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.76,0:21:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.77,0:21:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How old are you, Yamamoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.24,0:21:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm 19 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.44,0:21:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. 19, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.08,0:21:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I would like you \Nto explain something to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.09,0:21:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.07,0:21:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, what kind of life \Nwould you describe as righteous?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The more I think about it, \Nthe less I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.33,0:21:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is the mother \Nof all tough questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.42,0:22:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think there is anyone in this day and age who can answer this question correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.51,0:22:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I can at least answer it for myself. \NFor some reason, I've always been a lucky man. {think he means "I've determined for myself what I consider an answer" or more simply "this is my personal, subjective opinion"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.05,0:22:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In my life, I had a chance to read Nichiren Daishonin's great works
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.87,0:22:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Buddhist philosophy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.08,0:22:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The rather long human lifespan \Npresents us with many problems along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.81,0:22:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For our time, it's food shortages,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.83,0:22:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,housing shortages, difficult circumstances, \Naccidents, and disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.45,0:22:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In this life, you never know \Nwhat may happen the very next moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.10,0:22:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even these worries
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.85,0:22:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,are like ripples on the water \Nand are rather easy to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.35,0:22:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There are more fundamental problems that cannot be resolved that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.12,0:22:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we solve the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.07,0:22:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of life and death in order to ensure the survival of human race?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.99,0:22:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.47,0:22:53.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,Life and death {生死}{left} \NBirth \NAging \NGetting frail{/falling ill} \NDying {生老病死と}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.10,0:22:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism talks about birth, aging, getting frail,{/falling ill} and dying, {the four inevitables in human life}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.28,0:22:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but unless we manage to resolve this question, \Nthe truly righteous life is unattainable. {unsure: 仏法では生老病死と言っているがこれが正しく解決されなければ真の正しい人生なんかあるはずがありません!}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You can apologize for being born,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.71,0:23:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can't help the fact \Nyou've been born forcefully into this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.34,0:23:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"I want to stay a 19-year-old girl forever."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.19,0:23:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've thought about not wanting to age many times myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.05,0:23:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But 40 or 50 years later, \Nwe all become those craggy old grannies. {lit: pickled ume - kinda looks like a dried persimmon so probably means "wrinkly"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.88,0:23:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this wasn't very thoughtful of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.59,0:23:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I say that I will never get sick, \NI still have a mortal body... {probably refers to the 3rd stage in four inevitables earlier}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.07,0:23:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With time, it'll grow frail.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.40,0:23:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, death, \Nwhich to many is the most unpalatable. {hope he means this by "really tough"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.51,0:23:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone prefers to think \Nthat they're going to live forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But even the young men who are present here \Nwon’t be alive 60 to 70 years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.37,0:23:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use saying \Nthat you don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.38,0:23:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter your position and your wealth,\Nor how strong your convictions are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.38,0:23:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.35,0:23:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is safe to say that no philosophy has ever
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.06,0:24:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,provided a correct and concrete solution to these important problems in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.09,0:24:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, even if you want to live a life of righteousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.50,0:24:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in reality, \Nyou have little to no control over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.34,0:24:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, Nichiren Daishonin has taught us how to solve all of life's difficult problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, he has given us specific instructions so that anyone, no matter how removed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.62,0:24:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,from religion he is, \Ncan surely attain such a state of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.28,0:24:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where else in the world can such a great philosophy be found?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.25,0:24:34.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,It seems he belongs to a sect that chants Nam Myoho Renge Kyo, but he is not a monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.64,0:24:36.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,What kind of person is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.55,0:24:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.62,0:24:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's good to ponder the question of what a righteous life is,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.88,0:24:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you have the time, why don't you try to study the Daishonin's Dharma
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.90,0:24:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and put it into practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.63,0:24:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still a young man. \NSomeday, the answer to the question
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.93,0:24:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is a righteous life will come to you naturally,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.63,0:24:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you like it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.93,0:24:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you this much for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.19,0:25:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask you one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.19,0:25:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about the Emperor?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.19,0:25:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. That's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.48,0:25:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhist law doesn't have any special provisions
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.51,0:25:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Emperor or the Imperial System.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.30,0:25:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think there is any need \Nto eradicate the Japanese Emperor's family,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.59,0:25:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which has existed for generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.31,0:25:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is there any need \Nto give it special treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.75,0:25:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The times have changed drastically.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.73,0:25:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see from the new constitution,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.34,0:25:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,sovereignty resides with the people, \Nwhile the Emperor remains a symbolic figure,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.42,0:25:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.85,0:25:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The question now is how can our people, \Nincluding the Emperor,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.04,0:25:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,rise up from the agony \Nof this defeat as soon as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.80,0:25:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and build a peaceful, tranquil, and cultured nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.33,0:25:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right? {probably "does this answer your question?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.33,0:26:02.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,He came up with an answer so quickly... \NAnd without the slightest hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.08,0:26:06.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,I feel like I can believe his arguments.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.10,0:26:11.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what kind of person is he to me? {unsure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.72,0:26:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.32,0:26:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.30,0:26:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a proverb in the Chinese Book of Rites that says, "Even if you agree, think again,"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.00,0:26:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and "Even if you don't agree, think again."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.37,0:26:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in what you said about studying and practicing as a young man,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.24,0:26:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so I will study under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.38,0:26:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to express my gratitude now \Nin the form of a poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.71,0:26:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's a clumsy impromptu poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.78,0:26:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Traveler, {from https://www.daisakuikeda.org/sub/resources/works/poet/springing.html}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.00,0:27:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,From whence do you come?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.22,0:27:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And where do you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.29,0:27:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The moon has set,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.83,0:27:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sun has not yet risen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.46,0:27:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the chaos of darkness before the dawn
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.25,0:27:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeking the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.34,0:27:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I advance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.55,0:27:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To dispel the dark clouds from my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.85,0:27:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To find a great tree unbowed by the tempest
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.56,0:27:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I gush forth from the Earth. {[like a Bodhisattva of the earth]}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.79,0:27:42.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi-kun, 19 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.07,0:27:48.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,"I gush forth from the Earth."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.00,0:27:50.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,From the earth, huh... {episode title}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.77,0:27:55.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I think they said Yamamoto-kun \Nsuffers from a lung disease. {lit: his chest is bad/wounded}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.46,0:27:58.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,No, he'll be fine. He's only 19. {idk what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.15,0:28:02.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,Ah, the sweet age of 19. \NI was still in Hokkaido.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.26,0:28:05.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,In Mayachi, Yubari county...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.78,0:28:05.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yubari{district}, Mayachi{town}{夕張・真谷地}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.83,0:28:09.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,Mayachi Elementary School {真谷地尋常小學校}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.45,0:28:13.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,Then, when I was 20 years old, \NI moved to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.81,0:28:20.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm 47 years old now, Yamamoto-kun is 19 years old, almost 20 actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.49,0:28:30.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In ten more days, on August 24th,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.22,0:28:34.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Young Yamamoto joined the Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.92,0:28:42.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,setting a new stage for the Common Path \Nat the turning point of history and time. {stage as in theater stage - idk what she means}
